PROC GLM DATA=WIFI PLOTS=(ALL);
     CLASS Distance Obstacle Number_Users;
     MODEL Speed = Distance | Obstacle | Number_Users / SS3;
     MEANS Distance | Obstacle | Number_Users;
     OUTPUT OUT=diag R=resid;
TITLE 'THREE FACTOR ANALYSIS OF VARIANCE FOR THE WIFI SPEED';

PROC UNIVARIATE DATA=diag NORMAL PLOTS;
     VAR resid;
TITLE 'Check for Normality Assumption';
RUN;

In [ ]:

The above output shows that the distribution of residuals is right skewed. So I am going to log-transform the data.

In [5]:
DATA WIFI_L;
     SET WIFI;
     LOG_Speed = LOG(Speed);
RUN;

PROC GLM DATA=WIFI_L PLOTS=(ALL);
     CLASS Distance Obstacle Number_Users;
     *TRANSFORM LOG(Speed);
     MODEL LOG_Speed = Distance | Obstacle | Number_Users / SS3;
     MEANS Distance | Obstacle | Number_Users;
     OUTPUT OUT=diag R=resid;
TITLE 'THREE FACTOR ANALYSIS OF VARIANCE FOR THE WIFI SPEED';

PROC UNIVARIATE DATA=diag NORMAL PLOTS;
     VAR resid;
TITLE 'Check for Normality Assumption';
RUN;

PROC GLM DATA=WIFI_L;
CLASS Distance Obstacle Number_Users;
MODEL LOG_Speed = Distance | Obstacle | Number_Users / SS3;
MEANS Distance | Obstacle | Number_Users /TUKEY ALPHA = .05 CLDIFF LINES;
LSMEANS Distance*Obstacle Distance*Number_Users Obstacle*Number_Users Distance*Obstacle*Number_Users / ADJUST = TUKEY;
ESTIMATE 'MU' INTERCEPT 1;
ESTIMATE "Distance 10" Distance 2 -1 -1 / DIVISOR = 3;
ESTIMATE "Distance 30" Distance -1 2 -1 / DIVISOR = 3;
ESTIMATE "Distance 50" Distance -1 -1 2 / DIVISOR = 3;

ESTIMATE "Obstacle 0" Obstacle 1 -1 / DIVISOR = 2;
ESTIMATE "Obstacle 1" Obstacle -1 1 / DIVISOR = 2;

ESTIMATE "Number_Users 1" 3 -1 -1 -1 / DIVISOR = 4;
ESTIMATE "Number_Users 2" -1 3 -1 -1 / DIVISOR = 4;
ESTIMATE "Number_Users 3" -1 -1 3 -1 / DIVISOR = 4;
ESTIMATE "Number_Users 4" -1 -1 -1 3 / DIVISOR = 4;
RUN;

DATA THREEWAY;
     INPUT LEVELA $ LEVELB $ LEVELC $ MEANEST;
DATALINES;
A1 B1 C1 2.22  A1 B1 C2 1.97  A1 B1 C3 1.67  A1 B1 C4 1.54  A1 B2 C1 2.42  A1 B2 C2 2.03  A1 B2 C3 1.68  A1 B2 C4 1.58  A2 B1 C1 2.4  A2 B1 C2 2.06  A2 B1 C3 1.74  A2 B1 C4 1.61  A2 B2 C1 2.29  A2 B2 C2 1.95  A2 B2 C3 1.55  A2 B2 C4 1.46  A3 B1 C1 2.41  A3 B1 C2 2  A3 B1 C3 1.73  A3 B1 C4 1.59  A3 B2 C1 2.26  A3 B2 C2 1.96  A3 B2 C3 1.4  A3 B2 C4 1.15
;
PROC GLMPOWER DATA=THREEWAY;
    CLASS LEVELA LEVELB LEVELC;
    MODEL MEANEST = LEVELA | LEVELB | LEVELC;
    POWER 
      STDDEV = 0.1189
      alpha = 0.05
      ntotal = 120
      power = . ;
   title 'Power analysis';
run;
PROC PRINT DATA=THREEWAY;
RUN;
